netspy (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release with PCAP-over-IP streaming support
  * Add real-time PCAP streaming over TCP (port 57012)
  * Implement Python CLI frontend with comprehensive options
  * Add automatic Wireshark integration (--wireshark option)
  * Include Python stream clients with scapy support
  * Add comprehensive Google Test unit test suite
  * Support multiple concurrent PCAP stream clients
  * Add comprehensive man page documentation
  * Include examples for traffic filtering and analysis
  * Thread-safe implementation with minimal performance overhead
  * Basic network traffic logging via LD_PRELOAD
  * PCAP file generation compatible with Wireshark
  * IPv4 and IPv6 support for TCP/UDP protocols
  * JSON-based function specification
  * CMake build system with installation support

 -- Dmitry Mikushin <dmitry@kernelgen.org>  Mon, 30 Dec 2024 19:00:00 +0000